(c)

I think the independence assumption is not reasonable because the temperature of Boston and NY will be affected by certain weather conditions at the same time since they are both located on the east coast of the US.

(a)

The assumptions I must make are 1. Each car results in having a problem or not having a problem 2. cars’ test results on electrical wiring are independent of each other 3. Cars have the same probability of having a problem

(c)

Is it likely?

No. It’s extremely unlikely that 30% of the cars have a problem because the probability of finding five or fewer cars having a problem in the given situation is almost 0%.
